"index_reference": "4808",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A deep red colour used interchangeably with scarlet and sometimes with purple. It has associations with blood and richness.</p>\n<h2>The richness of crimson used for ornamentation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:3-Exod25:4\">EXO 25:3–25:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:6\">EXO 28:6</a></strong> <em>It was used extensively in the construction of the tabernacle</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:7\">2CH 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:14\">2CH 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:14\">2CH 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Crimson associated with splendour and prosperity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:24\">2SA 1:24</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:16\">REV 18:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:21\">PRO 31:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:30\">JER 4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:3\">NAM 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:28\">MAT 27:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:17\">MRK 15:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:12\">REV 18:12</a></p>\n<h2>Crimson associated with blood and sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:18\">ISA 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:3-Lev14:6\">LEV 14:3–14:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:49-Lev14:53\">LEV 14:49–14:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:6\">NUM 19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:1-Isa63:3\">ISA 63:1–63:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:19\">HEB 9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3-Rev17:4\">REV 17:3–17:4</a></p>\n<h2>Everyday use of the colour crimson</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:28\">GEN 38:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:17-Josh2:18\">JOS 2:17–2:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:3\">SNG 4:3</a></p>",
